tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE UserInteractions (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    interaction_date DATE,
    interaction_time TIME,
    visualization_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_duration INTERVAL
)

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
user_id INT,
interaction_type VARCHAR(255),
interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
visualization_id INT);

CREATE TABLE visualization_design (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
visualization_name VARCHAR(255),
created_by VARCHAR(255),
creation_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
last_modified_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
engagement_metrics INT,
feedback TEXT);

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    visualization_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  registration_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE visualizations (
  visualization_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  visualization_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  created_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  user_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
  interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  visualization_id INT,
  interaction_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (visualization_id) REFERENCES visualizations(visualization_id)
)

CREATE TABLE visualization_design (
  design_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  visualization_id INT,
  design_data JSONB NOT NULL,
  design_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  FOREIGN KEY (visualization_id) REFERENCES visualizations(visualization_id)
)

CREATE TABLE user_interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(255),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    visualization_id INT
)

CREATE TABLE visualizations (
    visualization_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    visualization_name VARCHAR(255),
    visualization_type VARCHAR(255),
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE user_engagement (
    engagement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    interaction_id INT,
    engagement_score INT,
    engagement_duration INT
)

CREATE TABLE data_visualization_design (
    design_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    visualization_id INT,
    designer_id INT,
    design_style VARCHAR(255),
    design_feedback TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE user_feedback (
    feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    visualization_id INT,
    feedback_text TEXT,
    feedback_timestamp TIMESTAMP
)
